cockpit-upside (1.0.4) noble; urgency=medium

  * Trends and Metrics charts now auto-refresh, so the pages work as a live
    dashboard. Trends rolls its 6h window; Metrics refreshes only while viewing
    the latest window (paused when zoomed or stepped into the past). Refreshes
    are self-scheduled (never stacking) and can be turned off.
  * Mobile: the breadcrumb collapses to a dropdown on narrow screens instead of
    wrapping; the logo tagline and masthead padding tighten on small phones; and
    the Control/Monitor toggle moves into the menu on the narrowest screens.
  * Setup wizard (mobile): the nav no longer paints over the masthead or its
    open menu, and the step number/label spacing is less cramped.

 -- Robert Sæther <robert4832@pm.me>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 15:06:42 +0000

cockpit-upside (1.0.3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Controls: redesigned panel. Capability-gated actions (only commands the UPS
    actually supports are shown), an action-card "danger zone" listing each raw
    NUT command behind a per-action confirmation with an optional delay, and a
    beeper toggle. The confirm button reads "… immediately" or "… in Ns" to
    match the delay field (empty = run now).
  * Controls: battery self-test shows a live status (running / idle) and surfaces
    the result — including the common case of a UPS that reports no pass/fail
    over USB. Per-section feedback so a result can't hide under an expanded
    danger zone.
  * Notifications: a Notifications step in the setup wizard; outbound mail is
    sent (and its prerequisites ensured) as the upsmon RUN_AS_USER notifier.
  * Masthead: mobile overflow menu + compact desktop band; a "Dashboard" home
    link in the per-UPS menu.
  * Dashboard header now reflows on small screens (breadcrumb + menu on top, the
    status/auth row left-aligned below), matching the metrics header.
  * Preferences (mode, remembered credentials, ranges) persist across a Cockpit
    logout. Danger-zone expand state is remembered per browser.

 -- Robert Sæther <robert4832@pm.me>  Wed, 03 Jun 2026 22:34:28 +0000

cockpit-upside (1.0.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Metrics: a "Go to now" item in the timeframe dropdown jumps the window back
    to the latest data after stepping into the past (or zooming), keeping the
    chosen range.

 -- Robert Sæther <robert4832@pm.me>  Tue, 02 Jun 2026 11:19:43 +0000

cockpit-upside (1.0.1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Remote history: a secondary host (a remote NUT source) can now plot the
    primary's history, read over the network from the primary's PCP pmproxy
    time-series REST API — no local archive needed. Configure a "Remote history"
    URL (+ optional HTTP Basic credentials) in Settings.
  * Metrics: Grafana-style two-tier time axis (a primary time/date/month tick
    row plus a day/month/year context band with boundary markers, all
    locale-aware); every range up to 1 year is now selectable; the line breaks
    across real data gaps instead of bridging them; gap-aware hover.
  * Setup wizard shows the version + a GitHub link; the per-UPS menu is renamed
    "Menu" (it's navigation, not just management).
  * Fixes: dropdown borders no longer paint over the sticky masthead on scroll;
    the "Protected hosts" card is correct on a secondary (the remote primary is
    labelled as such, not "this host"); fix a hang reading the series API over
    cockpit.http (a GET needs an explicit empty body).

 -- Robert Sæther <robert4832@pm.me>  Tue, 02 Jun 2026 10:18:43 +0000

cockpit-upside (1.0.0) noble; urgency=medium

  * Control: instant commands (upscmd, risk-tiered with a danger zone),
    writable variables (upsrw Configuration view), and clean shutdown on low
    battery (upsmon Shutdown step + per-UPS settings, opt-in killpower).
  * Event notifications (upsmon NOTIFY) via a pluggable adapter that defaults
    to the system mailer.
  * Guided setup wizard (NUT modes) covering USB / SNMP / serial devices, and
    one-click "enable history" (PCP).
  * Per-UPS Manage menu, remote-upsd (name@host) support, and a version
    indicator.

